# TTD architecture

## Layering

- **`ttd.core`** — all billing/ledger domain logic, ferro-orm models, async services
- **`ttd.cli` / `ttd.api` / `ttd.tui`** — thin adapters only: parse input → `await` core → format output

Never implement domain rules, rounding, or persistence in surface packages.

## Async

- Core services and DB access are `async`
- CLI uses cyclopts async commands; API uses Litestar lifespan for DB init; TUI calls async core helpers from async hooks

## Surface rollout (see `docs/roadmap.md`)

- M1–M4: CLI-first ledger + CSV export; domain logic only in core
- M5–M7: TUI, PDF/Markdown invoices, API — thin adapters; no business logic ahead of core services for each milestone

